\f1\fs64 \cf3 Exodus 
\b0\fs24 \cf2 \

\f2\b\fs64 \cf4 1
\b0\fs26 \cf2 Now these are the names of the children of Israel who came to Egypt; each man and his household came with Jacob: 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah; 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin; 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Dan, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 All those who were descendants of Jacob were seventy persons (for Joseph was in Egypt already). 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And Joseph died, all his brothers, and all that generation.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf3 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But the children of Israel were fruitful and increased abundantly, multiplied and grew 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf2 exceedingly mighty; and the land was filled with them.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf3 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now there arose a new king over Egypt, who did not know Joseph. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And he said to his people, "Look, the people of the children of Israel are more and mightier than we; 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 come, let us deal shrewdly with them, lest they multiply, and it happen, in the event of war, that they also join our enemies and fight against us, and so go up out of the land." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Therefore they set taskmasters over them to afflict them with their burdens. And they built for Pharaoh supply cities, Pithom and Raamses. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But the more they afflicted them, the more they multiplied and grew. And they were in dread of the children of Israel. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the Egyptians made the children of Israel serve with rigor. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And they made their lives bitter with hard bondage--in mortar, in brick, and in all manner of service in the field. All their service in which they made them serve was with rigor. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then the king of Egypt spoke to the Hebrew midwives, of whom the name of one was Shiphrah and the name of the other Puah; 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 and he said, "When you do the duties of a midwife for the Hebrew women, and see them on the birthstools, if it is a son, then you shall kill him; but if it is a daughter, then she shall live." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But the midwives feared God, and did not do as the king of Egypt commanded them, but saved the male children alive. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the king of Egypt called for the midwives and said to them, "Why have you done this thing, and saved the male children alive?" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the midwives said to Pharaoh, "Because the Hebrew women are not like the Egyptian women; for they are lively and give birth before the midwives come to them." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Therefore God dealt well with the midwives, and the people multiplied and grew very mighty. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And so it was, because the midwives feared God, that He provided households for them. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So Pharaoh commanded all his people, saying, "Every son who is born you shall cast into the river, and every daughter you shall save alive." 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs64 \cf4 2
\b0\fs26 \cf2 And a man of the house of Levi went and took as wife a daughter of Levi.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf3 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the woman conceived and bore a son. And when she saw that he was a beautiful 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf2 child, she hid him three months. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But when she could no longer hide him, she took an ark of bulrushes for him, daubed it with asphalt and pitch, put the child in it, and laid it in the reeds by the river's bank. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And his sister stood afar off, to know what would be done to him. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then the daughter of Pharaoh came down to bathe at the river. And her maidens walked along the riverside; and when she saw the ark among the reeds, she sent her maid to get it. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And when she opened it, she saw the child, and behold, the baby wept. So she had compassion on him, and said, "This is one of the Hebrews' children." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then his sister said to Pharaoh's daughter, "Shall I go and call a nurse for you from the Hebrew women, that she may nurse the child for you?" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And Pharaoh's daughter said to her, "Go." So the maiden went and called the child's mother. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Pharaoh's daughter said to her, "Take this child away and nurse him for me, and I will give you your wages." So the woman took the child and nursed him. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the child grew, and she brought him to Pharaoh's daughter, and he became her son. So she called his name Moses, saying, "Because I drew him out of the water." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now it came to pass in those days, when Moses was grown, that he went out to his brethren and looked at their burdens. And he saw an Egyptian beating a Hebrew, one of his brethren. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So he looked this way and that way, and when he saw no one, he killed the Egyptian and hid him in the sand. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And when he went out the second day, behold, two Hebrew men were fighting, and he said to the one who did the wrong, "Why are you striking your companion?" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then he said, "Who made you a prince and a judge over us? Do you intend to kill me as you killed the Egyptian?" So Moses feared and said, "Surely this thing is known!" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 When Pharaoh heard of this matter, he sought to kill Moses. But Moses fled from the face of Pharaoh and dwelt in the land of Midian; and he sat down by a well. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters. And they came and drew water, and they filled the troughs to water their father's flock. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then the shepherds came and drove them away; but Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 When they came to Reuel their father, he said, "How is it that you have come so soon today?" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And they said, "An Egyptian delivered us from the hand of the shepherds, and he also drew enough water for us and watered the flock." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So he said to his daughters, "And where is he? Why is it that you have left the man? Call him, that he may eat bread." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Moses was content to live with the man, and he gave Zipporah his daughter to Moses. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And she bore him a son. He called his name Gershom, for he said, "I have been a stranger in a foreign land." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now it happened in the process of time that the king of Egypt died. Then the children of Israel groaned because of the bondage, and they cried out; and their cry came up to God because of the bondage. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So God heard their groaning, and God remembered His covenant with Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And God looked upon the children of Israel, and God acknowledged them.\uc0\u8232 
\b\fs64 \cf4 3
\b0\fs26 \cf2 Now Moses was tending the flock of Jethro his father-in-law, the priest of Midian. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf2 And he led the flock to the back of the desert, and came to Horeb, the mountain of God. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the Angel of the LORD appeared to him in a flame of fire from the midst of a bush. So he looked, and behold, the bush was burning with fire, but the bush was not consumed. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Moses said, "I will now turn aside and see this great sight, why the bush does not burn." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So when the LORD saw that he turned aside to look, God called to him from the midst of the bush and said, "Moses, Moses!" And he said, "Here I am." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then He said, "Do not draw near this place. Take your sandals off your feet, for the place where you stand is holy ground." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Moreover He said, "I am the God of your father--the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob." And Moses hid his face, for he was afraid to look upon God. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the LORD said: "I have surely seen the oppression of My people who are in Egypt, and have heard their cry because of their taskmasters, for I know their sorrows. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So I have come down to deliver them out of the hand of the Egyptians, and to bring them up from that land to a good and large land, to a land flowing with milk and honey, to the place of the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Amorites and the Perizzites and the Hivites and the Jebusites. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now therefore, behold, the cry of the children of Israel has come to Me, and I have also seen the oppression with which the Egyptians oppress them. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Come now, therefore, and I will send you to Pharaoh that you may bring My people, the children of Israel, out of Egypt." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But Moses said to God, "Who am I that I should go to Pharaoh, and that I should bring the children of Israel out of Egypt?" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So He said, "I will certainly be with you. And this shall be a sign to you that I have sent you: When you have brought the people out of Egypt, you shall serve God on this mountain." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Moses said to God, "Indeed, when I come to the children of Israel and say to them, "The God of your fathers has sent me to you,' and they say to me, "What is His name?' what shall I say to them?" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And God said to Moses, "I AM WHO I AM." And He said, "Thus you shall say to the children of Israel, "I AM has sent me to you."' 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Moreover God said to Moses, "Thus you shall say to the children of Israel: "The LORD God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has sent me to you. This is My name forever, and this is My memorial to all generations.' 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Go and gather the elders of Israel together, and say to them, "The LORD God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, of Isaac, and of Jacob, appeared to me, saying, "I have surely visited you and seen what is done to you in Egypt; 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 and I have said I will bring you up out of the affliction of Egypt to the land of the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Amorites and the Perizzites and the Hivites and the Jebusites, to a land flowing with milk and honey."' 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then they will heed your voice; and you shall come, you and the elders of Israel, to the king of Egypt; and you shall say to him, "The LORD God of the Hebrews has met with us; and now, please, let us go three days' journey into the wilderness, that we may sacrifice to the LORD our God.' 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But I am sure that the king of Egypt will not let you go, no, not even by a mighty hand. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So I will stretch out My hand and strike Egypt with all My wonders which I will do in its midst; and after that he will let you go. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And I will give this people favor in the sight of the Egyptians; and it shall be, when you go, that you shall not go empty-handed. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But every woman shall ask of her neighbor, namely, of her who dwells near her house, articles of silver, articles of gold, and clothing; and you shall put them on your sons and on your daughters. So you shall plunder the Egyptians." 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs64 \cf4 4
\b0\fs26 \cf2 Then Moses answered and said, "But suppose they will not believe me or listen to my voice; suppose they say, "The LORD has not appeared to you."' 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the LORD said to him, "What is that in your hand?" He said, "A rod."\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf3 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And He said, "Cast it on the ground." So he cast it on the ground, and it became a 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf2 serpent; and Moses fled from it. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Reach out your hand and take it by the tail" (and he reached out his hand and caught it, and it became a rod in his hand), 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "that they may believe that the LORD God of their fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has appeared to you." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Furthermore the LORD said to him, "Now put your hand in your bosom." And he put his hand in his bosom, and when he took it out, behold, his hand was leprous, like snow. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And He said, "Put your hand in your bosom again." So he put his hand in his bosom again, and drew it out of his bosom, and behold, it was restored like his other flesh. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "Then it will be, if they do not believe you, nor heed the message of the first sign, that they may believe the message of the latter sign. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And it shall be, if they do not believe even these two signs, or listen to your voice, that you shall take water from the river and pour it on the dry land. The water which you take from the river will become blood on the dry land." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Moses said to the LORD, "O my Lord, I am not eloquent, neither before nor since You have spoken to Your servant; but I am slow of speech and slow of tongue." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the LORD said to him, "Who has made man's mouth? Or who makes the mute, the deaf, the seeing, or the blind? Have not I, the LORD? 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now therefore, go, and I will be with your mouth and teach you what you shall say." 
\fs16 \cf3 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But he said, "O my Lord, please send by the hand of whomever else You may 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf2 send." 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the anger of the LORD was kindled against Moses, and He said: "Is not Aaron the Levite your brother? I know that he can speak well. And look, he is also coming out to meet you. When he sees you, he will be glad in his heart. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now you shall speak to him and put the words in his mouth. And I will be with your mouth and with his mouth, and I will teach you what you shall do. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So he shall be your spokesman to the people. And he himself shall be as a mouth for you, and you shall be to him as God. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall take this rod in your hand, with which you shall do the signs." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So Moses went and returned to Jethro his father-in-law, and said to him, "Please let me go and return to my brethren who are in Egypt, and see whether they are still alive." And Jethro said to Moses, "Go in peace." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Now the LORD said to Moses in Midian, "Go, return to Egypt; for all the men who sought your life are dead." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Moses took his wife and his sons and set them on a donkey, and he returned to the land of Egypt. And Moses took the rod of God in his hand. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the LORD said to Moses, "When you go back to Egypt, see that you do all those wonders before Pharaoh which I have put in your hand. But I will harden his heart, so that he will not let the people go. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then you shall say to Pharaoh, "Thus says the LORD: "Israel is My son, My firstborn. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So I say to you, let My son go that he may serve Me. But if you refuse to let him go, indeed I will kill your son, your firstborn.""' 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And it came to pass on the way, at the encampment, that the LORD met him and sought to kill him. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Zipporah took a sharp stone and cut off the foreskin of her son and cast it at Moses' feet, and said, "Surely you are a husband of blood to me!" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 26
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So He let him go. Then she said, "You are a husband of blood!"--because of the circumcision. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 27
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the LORD said to Aaron, "Go into the wilderness to meet Moses." So he went and met him on the mountain of God, and kissed him. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 28
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So Moses told Aaron all the words of the LORD who had sent him, and all the signs which He had commanded him. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 29
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then Moses and Aaron went and gathered together all the elders of the children of Israel. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 30
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And Aaron spoke all the words which the LORD had spoken to Moses. Then he did the signs in the sight of the people. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 31
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the people believed; and when they heard that the LORD had visited the children of Israel and that He had looked on their affliction, then they bowed their heads and worshiped. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs64 \cf4 5
\b0\fs26 \cf2 Afterward Moses and Aaron went in and told Pharaoh, "Thus says the LORD God of Israel: "Let My people go, that they may hold a feast to Me in the wilderness."' 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And Pharaoh said, "Who is the LORD, that I should obey His voice to let Israel go? I do not know the LORD, nor will I let Israel go." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So they said, "The God of the Hebrews has met with us. Please, let us go three days' journey into the desert and sacrifice to the LORD our God, lest He fall upon us with pestilence or with the sword." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then the king of Egypt said to them, "Moses and Aaron, why do you take the people from their work? Get back to your labor." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And Pharaoh said, "Look, the people of the land are many now, and you make them rest from their labor!" 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So the same day Pharaoh commanded the taskmasters of the people and their officers, saying, 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "You shall no longer give the people straw to make brick as before. Let them go and gather straw for themselves. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall lay on them the quota of bricks which they made before. You shall not reduce it. For they are idle; therefore they cry out, saying, "Let us go and sacrifice to our God.' 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Let more work be laid on the men, that they may labor in it, and let them not regard false words." 
