\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 33
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 They shall eat those things with which the atonement was made, to consecrate and to sanctify them; but an outsider shall not eat them, because they are holy. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 34
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And if any of the flesh of the consecration offerings, or of the bread, remains until the morning, then you shall burn the remainder with fire. It shall not be eaten, because it is holy. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 35
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "Thus you shall do to Aaron and his sons, according to all that I have commanded you. Seven days you shall consecrate them. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 36
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall offer a bull every day as a sin offering for atonement. You shall cleanse the altar when you make atonement for it, and you shall anoint it to sanctify it. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 37
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Seven days you shall make atonement for the altar and sanctify it. And the altar shall be most holy. Whatever touches the altar must be holy. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 38
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "Now this is what you shall offer on the altar: two lambs of the first year, day by day continually. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 39
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 One lamb you shall offer in the morning, and the other lamb you shall offer at twilight. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 40
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 With the one lamb shall be one-tenth of an ephah of flour mixed with one-fourth of a hin of pressed oil, and one-fourth of a hin of wine as a drink offering. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 41
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the other lamb you shall offer at twilight; and you shall offer with it the grain offering and the drink offering, as in the morning, for a sweet aroma, an offering made by fire to the LORD. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 42
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 This shall be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations at the door of the tabernacle of meeting before the LORD, where I will meet you to speak with you. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 43
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And there I will meet with the children of Israel, and the tabernacle shall be sanctified by My glory. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 44
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So I will consecrate the tabernacle of meeting and the altar. I will also consecrate both Aaron and his sons to minister to Me as priests. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 45
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 I will dwell among the children of Israel and will be their God.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf3 \up13 46
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And they shall know that I am the LORD their God, who brought them up out of the 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf2 land of Egypt, that I may dwell among them. I am the LORD their God.\uc0\u8232 
\b\fs64 \cf4 30
\b0\fs26 \cf2 "You shall make an altar to burn incense on; you shall make it of acacia wood. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 2
