\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall overlay its top, its sides all around, and its horns with pure gold; and you shall make for it a molding of gold all around. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Two gold rings you shall make for it, under the molding on both its sides. You shall place them on its two sides, and they will be holders for the poles with which to bear it. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 You shall make the poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf3 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall put it before the veil that is before the ark of the Testimony, before the 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf2 mercy seat that is over the Testimony, where I will meet with you. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "Aaron shall burn on it sweet incense every morning; when he tends the lamps, he shall burn incense on it. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And when Aaron lights the lamps at twilight, he shall burn incense on it, a perpetual incense before the LORD throughout your generations. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 You shall not offer strange incense on it, or a burnt offering, or a grain offering; nor shall you pour a drink offering on it. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And Aaron shall make atonement upon its horns once a year with the blood of the sin offering of atonement; once a year he shall make atonement upon it throughout your generations. It is most holy to the LORD." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying: 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "When you take the census of the children of Israel for their number, then every man shall give a ransom for himself to the LORD, when you number them, that there may be no plague among them when you number them. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 This is what everyone among those who are numbered shall give: half a shekel according to the shekel of the sanctuary (a shekel is twenty gerahs). The half-shekel shall be an offering to the LORD. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Everyone included among those who are numbered, from twenty years old and above, shall give an offering to the LORD. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 The rich shall not give more and the poor shall not give less than half a shekel, when you give an offering to the LORD, to make atonement for yourselves. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall take the atonement money of the children of Israel, and shall appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of meeting, that it may be a memorial for the children of Israel before the LORD, to make atonement for yourselves." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying: 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "You shall also make a laver of bronze, with its base also of bronze, for washing. You shall put it between the tabernacle of meeting and the altar. And you shall put water in it, 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 for Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet in water from it. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 When they go into the tabernacle of meeting, or when they come near the altar to minister, to burn an offering made by fire to the LORD, they shall wash with water, lest they die. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 So they shall wash their hands and their feet, lest they die. And it shall be a statute forever to them--to him and his descendants throughout their generations." 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Moreover the LORD spoke to Moses, saying: 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "Also take for yourself quality spices--five hundred shekels of liquid myrrh, half as much sweet-smelling cinnamon (two hundred and fifty shekels), two hundred and fifty shekels of sweet-smelling cane, 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 five hundred shekels of cassia, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, and a hin of olive oil. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall make from these a holy anointing oil, an ointment compounded according to the art of the perfumer. It shall be a holy anointing oil. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 26
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 With it you shall anoint the tabernacle of meeting and the ark of the Testimony; 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 27
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 the table and all its utensils, the lampstand and its utensils, and the altar of incense; 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 28
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and the laver and its base. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 29
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 You shall consecrate them, that they may be most holy; whatever touches them must be holy. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 30
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they may minister to Me as priests. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 31
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 "And you shall speak to the children of Israel, saying: "This shall be a holy anointing oil to Me throughout your generations. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 32
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 It shall not be poured on man's flesh; nor shall you make any other like it, according to its composition. It is holy, and it shall be holy to you. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 33
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Whoever compounds any like it, or whoever puts any of it on an outsider, shall be cut off from his people."' 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 34
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And the LORD said to Moses: "Take sweet spices, stacte and onycha and galbanum, and pure frankincense with these sweet spices; there shall be equal amounts of each. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 35
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 You shall make of these an incense, a compound according to the art of the perfumer, salted, pure, and holy. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 36
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 And you shall beat some of it very fine, and put some of it before the Testimony in the tabernacle of meeting where I will meet with you. It shall be most holy to you. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 37
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 But as for the incense which you shall make, you shall not make any for yourselves, according to its composition. It shall be to you holy for the LORD. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs16 \cf3 \up13 38
\fs26 \cf2 \up0 Whoever makes any like it, to smell it, he shall be cut off from his people." 
